---
import ResponsiveLayout from "../layouts/ResponsiveLayout.astro";
import SkillCard from "./SkillCard.astro";
import Rust from "simple-icons-astro/Rust";
import Kotlin from "simple-icons-astro/Kotlin";
import TypeScript from "simple-icons-astro/Typescript";
---

<section class="section-image skills-bg" id="skills">
    <div class="img-overlay"></div>

    <div class="skills-inner max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="section-heading mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-3xl! font-bold text-white pb-1">Skills</h2>
            <p class="lead text-2xl font-normal! text-center mb-4">
                A little more about my work skills in specific areas
            </p>
            <hr />
        </div>

        <ResponsiveLayout class="flex flex-row justify-center w-full">
            <SkillCard>
                <Rust size="3rem" />
                <h2>Rust</h2>
                <p>
                    I&nbsp;try to switch to using this language in all server-side
                    parts of my projects, as well as native and cpu-bound tasks.
                    I&nbsp;really like its speed and philosophy of working with
                    memory. I&nbsp;use it together with tauri for gui and axum
                    for web applications. I&nbsp;also actively use SeaOEM and Tokio.
                    For example, using Rust, I&nbsp;made Vanitron, a service for
                    finding beautiful crypto wallets. Another example is
                    RuinaCounter, a small web service for monitoring offline streamers.
                </p>
            </SkillCard>
            <SkillCard>
                <Kotlin size="3rem" />
                <h2>Kotlin</h2>
                <p>
                    My main language I&nbsp;use for mobile and sometimes backend
                    development. I&nbsp;familiar with kotlin coroutines and kotlin
                    multiplatform. My main project in this language is a
                    long-term pet project for the maiapp application, which is
                    fully written in kotlin, using mvvm. The server part
                    is developed using ktor server. I&nbsp;like the syntax of
                    this language and the way its coroutines work.
                </p>
            </SkillCard>
            <SkillCard>
                <TypeScript size="3rem" />
                <h2>TypeScript</h2>
                <p>
                    As you can see on this page, sometimes I&nbsp;develop websites.
                    I&nbsp;prefer working with TypeScript and React or Astro for
                    frontend development. However, I&nbsp;don't really like
                    working with TypeScript and JavaScript, so I&nbsp;try to use
                    it only in the frontend part. For example, I&nbsp;contributed
                    to the Anix project by adding functionality that I&nbsp;lacked,
                    or I&nbsp;developed several custom websites.
                </p>
            </SkillCard>
        </ResponsiveLayout>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    .img-overlay {
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        background: #111111;
        opacity: 0.7;
    }

    .skills-bg {
        background: #151515 url("/media/IMG_6911.JPG") no-repeat center center;
        background-size: cover;
        height: auto;
    }

    .skills-inner {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
        padding-top: 0;
        padding-bottom: 0;
    }

    .skills-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
        gap: 2rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .skills-grid {
            grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        }
    }

    @media (max-width: 480px) {
        .skills-grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .skills-bg {
            background: #151515 url("/media/IMG_6911.JPG") no-repeat top center;
            background-size: cover;
        }
    }
</style>
